31/10/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Starting in December, Romania will take over the rotating presidency of the Commission for the Protection of the Black Sea Against Pollution from Turkey.
The decision, announced Thursday (30 October), was made during the commission meeting in Istanbul.
Representatives of Bulgaria, Georgia, Romania, Russia, Turkey and the Ukraine also signed an intervention plan for emergency situations, such as oil spills in the Black Sea.
(ACT Media - 31/10/03;
Rompres - 30/10/03)
